<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">I don&#x27;t think nix is that hard for this particular use case. Installing nix on other distros is pretty easy, and once it&#x27;s installed you just do something like this<p><pre><code>    #! &#x2F;usr&#x2F;bin&#x2F;env nix-shell
    #! nix-shell -i bash -p imagemagick cowsay

    # scale image by 50%
    convert &quot;$1&quot; -scale 50% &quot;$1.s50.jpg&quot; &amp;&amp;
    cowsay &quot;done $1.q50.jpg&quot;
</code></pre>
Sure all of nixos and packaging for nix is a challenge, but just using it for a shell script is not too bad</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371081&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388%2344371081" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
