<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">This is very cool. I’ve stuck with built-in <i>python3 -m pip</i> and <i>python3 -m venv</i> for a long time, but <i>uv</i> offers performance improvements, covers the <i>pyenv</i> use case, and seems to have good momentum in the community.<p>Like <i>pyenv</i>, <i>uv</i> can be installed easily on macOS (via Homebrew). Unlike <i>pyenv</i>, <i>uv</i> also supports Windows (via WinGet). I’m hoping we’ll soon see <i>uv</i> in Linux package repos as well.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371988&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388%2344371988" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
