<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">So far I&#x27;ve only run into one minor ergonomic issue when using `uv run --script` with embedded metadata which is that sometimes I want to test changes to the script via the Python REPL, but that&#x27;s a bit harder to do since you have to run something like:<p><pre><code>  $ uv run --python=3.13 --with-requirements &lt;(uv export --script script.py) -- python
  &gt;&gt;&gt; from script import X
</code></pre>
I&#x27;d love if there were something more ergonomic like:<p><pre><code>  $ uv run --with-script script.py python
</code></pre>
Edit: this is better:<p><pre><code>  $ &quot;$(uv python find --script script.py)&quot;
  &gt;&gt;&gt; from script import X
</code></pre>
That fires up the correct python and venv for the script. You probably have to run the script once to create it.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371129&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388%2344371129" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
</table></td></tr><tr class="athing comtr" id="44371734"><td><table border="0">  <tr>    <td class='ind' indent='1'><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="40"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks">
      <center><a id='up_44371734' href='vote?id=44371734&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center>    </td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=dkdcio" class="hnuser">dkdcio</a> <span class="age" title="2025-06-24T22:32:31 1750804351"><a href="item?id=44371734">41 minutes ago</a></span> <span id="unv_44371734"></span><span class="navs"> | <a href="#44371129" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">parent</a> | <a href="#44371484" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">next</a> <a class="togg clicky" id="44371734" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)">[–]</a><span class="onstory"></span></span></span></div><br>
