<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">&gt; it&#x27;s defined in both .python-version and pyproject.toml<p>The `requires-version` field in `pyproject.toml` defines a <i>range</i> of compatible versions, while `.python-version` defines the specific version you want to use for development. If you create a new project with uv init, they&#x27;ll look similar (&gt;=3.13 and 3.13 today), but over time `requires-version` usually lags behind `.python-version` and defines the <i>minimum</i> supported Python version for the project. `requires-version` also winds up in your package metadata and can affect your callers&#x27; dependency resolution, for example if your published v1 supports Python 3.[old] but your v2 does not.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371165&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388%2344371165" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
