<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">The upside in Python is that dependencies tend to be more coarse grained and things break less when you update. With JS you have to be on the treadmill constantly to avoid bitrot, and because packages tend to be so small and dependency trees so large, there&#x27;s a lot of potential points of failure when updating anything.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371476&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388%2344371476" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
