<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">The bigger problem in Python has been its slowness and reliance on C dependencies.<p>Maven solved Java packaging circa 2005, for example. Yes, XML is verbose, but it&#x27;s an implementation detail. Python still lags on many fronts, 20 years later.<p>An example: even now it makes 0 sense to me why virtual envs are not designed and supposed to be portable between machines with the same architecture (!). Or why venvs need to be activated with shell-variety specific code.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371637&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388%2344371637" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
