<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">uvx is useful to run scripts inside PyPi packages. It does not support running Python scripts directly<p>You can use uvx run scripts with a combination of the --with flag to specify the dependencies and invoking python directly. For e.g<p>uvx --with youtube-transcript-api python transcript.py<p>But you wont get the benefit of PEP 723 metadata.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44370677&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44369388%2344370677" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
